OL,5,C` ABI
OL,7,FHome insurance claims for weather-
OL,8,Frelated damage reached a record #573
OL,9,Fmillion last year, according to the
OL,10,FAssociation of British Insurers (ABI).
OL,12,FThis was over a third (36%) higher
OL,13,Fthan in 2022, when the total was #421
OL,14,Fmillion.
OL,16,FThe rise was largely fuelled by the
OL,17,Fsuccession of storms, including Babet,
OL,18,FCiaran and Debi, according to the
OL,19,Fassociation, whose records on weather-
OL,20,Frelated domestic claims go back to
OL,21,F2017.
