OL,5,C` ABI
OL,7,FHomeowners' storm damage claims,
OL,8,Fincluding those for high winds,
OL,9,Ftotalled #133 million, with flooding
OL,10,Fadding #286 million. A further #153
OL,11,Fmillion of weather claims came from
OL,12,Fburst pipes, most of which happened in
OL,13,Fthe first three months of 2023 at the
OL,14,Ftail end of a cold winter.
OL,16,FThe average weather-related payout for
OL,17,Fhome insurance last year was
OL,18,Fapproaching #5,000, at #4,916. This
OL,19,Fwas a jump compared with 2022, when
OL,20,Fthe figure was #3,077.
